articles.contents:
About Me
Hello! My name is Rachel Heiss, and I’m a home
schooled sophomore in high school. I have five younger siblings and live
near Atlanta, Georgia. I enjoy reading, writing, baking, Marvel movies,
and listening to musicals, podcasts, and Taylor Swift.
About the Project
Working on title I’m also working on a more solid idea but
I’m looking at ticket price, seats in theatre vs. seats sold, number of
previews, and potential gross of broadway shows since 1985.
Goals
See what shows are the most popular over time
Potential gross for shows only starts showing up in the data in
1995

See how average ticket price changed over time
“This is data science” ~Preceptor “Kane’s Free High School Data
Science Bootcamp”
